<m0>   Mulholland Falls<m0> (R)<ep>
   <m0>Best for: <m0>Adults only<ep>
   <m0>Watch out for<m0>: Lots of profanity, nudity, explicit sexual situations, violence, adult issues<ep>
   <m0>What happens<m0>: This is a drama about four no-nonsense cops in an elite unit of the LAPD in the early 1950s. They make their own rules and get away with it until a routine murder reveals some dark secrets. While the cast is <m1> <m0>impressive (--) Nick Nolte, Melanie Griffith, Chazz Palminteri, Chris Penn and John Malkovich (--) the movie is a disappointment. Nolte smokes so many cigarettes it's as if he's doing a tobacco commercial.<ep>
