<m0>   <m0>The Pallbearer <m0>(PG-13)<ql>
<m1>   <ep>
<m0>   Best for: <m0>Ages 12 and up. David Schwimmer has a multitude of fans from the television series <m0>Friends<m0>, so children this age will definitely want to go.<ep>
<m0>   Watch out for: <m0>There is a suicide involved, although it's only discussed, not shown. Discreet sex scenes.<ep>
   <m0>What happens:<m0> Tom Thompson (Schwimmer) is a 25-ish architect schlump who lives at home with Mom (Carol Kane) and can't find work. He spends Tuesday nights bowling with his pals. Then he gets a phone call from a distressed mother (Barbara Hershey) who tells him that her son, his old schoolmate Bill has committed suicide. She asks Tom to be a pallbearer. The problem is that he cannot remember Bill. Nonetheless, he has a fling with Mrs. Abernathy, and he begins romancing an old schoolmate (Gwyneth Paltrow). <m1> <m0>Predictable complications ensue.<ql>
